          <LEXCollocations>
            <LEXCollocation>ἐπαίρω τὴν κεφαλήν</LEXCollocation>
          </LEXCollocations>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-11 10:32:06" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to raise up the head) to demonstrate courage in the face of danger or adversity</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to have courage</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to lift the head</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>A literal rendering of ἐπαίρω τὴν κεφαλήν ‘to lift up the head’ can be misleading in some languages, since the expression may be an idiom meaning ‘to be proud’ or ‘to try to take precedence over others.’ A more satisfactory equivalent in some languages may be ‘to look up.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
          <LEXReferences>
            <LEXReference>04202102800014</LEXReference>
          </LEXReferences>
          <LEXVideos/>
        </LEXMeaning>
