              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to lift one’s heel against) to oppose someone by turning against such a person, possibly with focus upon the initial aspect of becoming opposed to</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to turn against</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to oppose</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages a convenient way of rendering ‘to turn against’ may be ‘to become an enemy of.’</Comments>
